item.title: Cup Organizer
item.description:
This is an organizer that is designed to organize two cups in a vertical position.
Cups like coffee mugs are not easy to organize since they have handles. Or some other cups with special shape also leads to the same problem.

The first thing that came to my mind is a round disk in which both sides could hold the cup's open edge. However, it may not able to fit in cups with different diameters. Then I tried to find some solution with more versatility.

I need to find some mechanism that could change its dimension in one direction by a motion in the other direction. Then the four-bar linkage mechanism came to my mind. Thus this organizer comes out with the combination of three sets of four-bar linkage mechanisms.

The plates of the organizer come in two different shapes. Besides, the dimensions of the shaft and holes may vary from different printing setups, some adjustments may need to be done to make the shaft and hole fit. In order to keep the axial position of the parts, it's better to keep the texture of the 3D printed shaft and holes.
item.author: winfordew

item.title: Gloomhaven JOTL token basket
item.description:
Basket to hold the damage tokens for Gloomhaven Jaws of the Lion. As the pictures show, the monster card and monster devider thing slide inside the basket. The little edges make sure that the tokens don't get mixed up. Besides that, there is a little bit of extra space around the monster card to fit a larger amount of tokens and muddle/strengthen/poison things.

I designed a basket for 6 and 10 monsters. Make sure to print it flat and use supports. Also make sure to remove all the supports with a scraper or something otherwise the monster card will not fit perfectly.

In the picture not all supports we removed yet, therefore it is not all fitting correctly.

I printed this in black PETG but PLA would also work fine.

item.title: Ender 3 Max PSU Cover Replacement for Noctua Fan Upgrade
item.description:
This PSU cover increases the depth of the PSU to allow for the installation of a Noctua NF-A6x25.

The cover is split into two parts to make it easier to print while still allowing the original bottom panel to fit over the PSU case.

I friction welded the two parts together for added rigidity but you could also use any adhesive like superglue or 3DGloop to hold them together.

It uses the original screws and mounts back onto the PSU just like the OEM part.

item.title: Work Rezax Hex Tool 17"/18"
item.description:
Hi,

This is a quick hex tool I drew up in order to screw down properly the hex cap on work rezax rims as they have a tendency to come loose.
There's a small pry bar on the end to help lift up the waffle upon removal.

Infill should be at least 20% but no more than 40% (although it's up to you), would much rather the tool break than the threads on the hex strip.

This works on both 17'' and 18'' hex caps both tall and short.

Designed to be printed without supports.

Let me know if there's anything that needs to be edited.
Step files available for editing.

Thanks.
item.author: ICEBLOCK

item.title: Proxxon Micromot 12V tools socket / plug for panel mount
item.description:
This is a plug shell for Proxxon Micromot series of tools, which operate on 12V power.

It has 2 halves which bolt together (4mm bolt fits in the hole), and for contacts, it uses butt connectors (without the plastic sleeve), similiar to https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3437152

The butt connectors should be solid all the way around (so not have a split to help crush them), and be a tight fit around the tools plugs poles.

I used butt connectors called "VT STV-B Butt connector, 1.5 - 2.5 mm²", bough from here: https://www.reichelt.com/de/en/butt-connector-1-5-2-5-mm-blue-vt-stv-b-p231400.html, however, there must be similiar connectors available elsewhere too, you might want to test others before ordering those if you find the shipping expensive.

The plug is designed to slide into a slot in a panel. I have however included the .blend file as well if you want to edit this more easily.
item.author: Okxa

item.title: Hotend adapter Creality CR6 SE to CR 10 / ENDER 3
item.description:
Due to the low availability of spare parts for CR6 i decided to make myself an adapter for hotend that i can mount hotend from creality cr 10. I have never done such things so process was very long and the result is awful, but it works! Works really well, my printer is making much better prints than before.

Dont do supports inside screw holes!

There are holes to mount a fan, but i found it works better when i mount fan on the hotend case.

I printed it using standard PLA, with ABS, adapter for sure will last much longer :)

Fell free to improve this model, he really needs this!

I used 0.4mm nozzle, i dont know if holes for screws dont gonna be to big with smaller nozzles.
